Crime, including robbery with violence, murder and consumuption of illicit alcohol, have gone up in Eldoret and other parts of Uasin Gishu. Governor Jackson Mandago has blamed security teams in the region over of deliberate laxity. He has asked IG Joseph Boinnet to investigate reports that some of the police officers in the region may be working with crimials to perpetrate crime. “We have high numbers of robberies and theft both in towns and rural areas and there is a lot to it going by the reports we are getting,” Mandago said. He threatened to sack county executives who attempt to sabotage his work through non performance. “This time everyone has to do their work, if the county assembly will recall any of you because of non performance, I will approve that”, he added. He told those not willing to work to 